      "excerpt": "I recently started adding an AI chatbot to this blog. At first, the idea was simple. As more posts accumulated, I wanted visitors to quickly understand things like \"what kind of developer is this person,\" \"what technolo…",
      "content": "How My Blog Chatbot Ended Up Using RAG\nI recently started adding an AI chatbot to this blog. At first, the idea was simple. As more posts accumulated, I wanted visitors to quickly understand things like \"what kind of developer is this person,\" \"what technologies does he mostly use,\" and \"which post should I read first\" without manually digging through every article. But once I started building it, the next set of questions came up almost immediately. Should I just ask an LLM to read the documents directly? Would static search be enough? Or did I really need embedding based RAG? At one point I tried exposing an embedding API through Lightning AI. The current direction is a Modal + PostgreSQL (pgvector) setup. This post is a record of that process: what I had to think through, and why I ended up making these choices. Blog chatbot development stages",
