      "title": "Productivity in the AI Era Depends More on Structure than Code: Why I Built lee-spec-kit",
      "url": "/en/blog/why-i-built-lee-spec-kit#so-lee-spec-kit-starts-by-shaping-the-documentation-flow",
      "excerpt": "That is why lee spec kit is designed to quickly bootstrap the basic documentation skeleton of a project and preserve a feature level flow through spec, plan, task, decision, and PR stages. The important part is not mere…",
      "content": "So lee-spec-kit Starts by Shaping the Documentation Flow\nThat is why lee spec kit is designed to quickly bootstrap the basic documentation skeleton of a project and preserve a feature level flow through spec, plan, task, decision, and PR stages. The important part is not merely providing many templates. The real goal is to let work context accumulate naturally and to make humans and AI share the same language for project state. What was decided, why it was decided, how far the work has progressed, and what should happen next should all remain visible in the document structure itself. Feature Workflow Pipeline This idea did not appear out of nowhere. I was influenced by the structure of spec kit and OpenSpec. Both projects were compelling because they organize work around specifications and preserve the thinking process before implementation. Looking at them made me more confident that this kind of approach becomes even stronger when combined with AI collaboration.",
      "sectionTitle": "So lee-spec-kit Starts by Shaping the Documentation Flow",
