      "id": "en/why-i-built-lee-spec-kit/closing-thoughts",
      "locale": "en",
      "slug": "why-i-built-lee-spec-kit",
      "title": "Productivity in the AI Era Depends More on Structure than Code: Why I Built lee-spec-kit",
      "url": "/en/blog/why-i-built-lee-spec-kit#closing-thoughts",
      "excerpt": "There is one thing this project made clearer to me. Productivity in the AI era will be harder and harder to explain through code generation ability alone. The more meaningful differences will likely come from how work i…",
      "content": "Closing Thoughts\nThere is one thing this project made clearer to me. Productivity in the AI era will be harder and harder to explain through code generation ability alone. The more meaningful differences will likely come from how work is divided, how documentation is structured, how clearly decisions and status are recorded, and how well that environment is designed for both humans and AI to use together. That is why I see lee spec kit not just as a CLI, but as an experiment in designing an AI friendly development environment. Using a strong model is not enough. You also have to design the structure that the model can work inside. In the long run, software productivity may become less about \"how fast can you generate code\" and more about \"how well can you design the structure of work.\" lee spec kit is my current answer to that question.",
