      "content": "Results\nLet's check the results of applying optimistic updates under slow network conditions in the browser. | Without Optimistic Updates | With Optimistic Updates | | : : | : : | | optimistic X | optimistic O | It is clear at a glance that the UI reflecting the optimistic update is faster. Since it is not feasible to apply optimistic updates to all requests, considering where it can be applied can lead to a better UX .",
