      "url": "/en/blog/mock-with-msw#why-mock",
      "excerpt": "In an ideal environment where frontend and backend can develop in sync, there would be no issues developing with real data. However, I have realized through various projects that this is not an easy condition during the…",
      "content": "Why Mock?\nIn an ideal environment where frontend and backend can develop in sync, there would be no issues developing with real data. However, I have realized through various projects that this is not an easy condition during the development phase. From the perspective of a frontend developer, there are inevitably parts where one has to wait when the backend is not implemented. Therefore, to complete the project on time, it would be more efficient to use and test the APIs that do not exist yet but will be created.",
